ke.go.moh.oec
Interface IService

All Known Implementing Classes:
Mediator
public interface IService

This interface is used for passing data requests and responses between the OpenEMRConnect (OEC) library and software using that library.

For client requests, this interface is implemented by the OEC library for the use of clients who have requests to send to a server.

For server software, this interface is implemented by the server object that will receive the request. If user software is only making client requests, it need not implement this interface.

Author:
Jim Grace

Method Detail

getData

java.lang.Object getData(int requestTypeId,
                         java.lang.Object requestData)
Request data through the service interface.

A client calls the getData method of the OEC library. In the library, this method will take the request, package it into a HL7 message, and deliver it to the server.

On the server side, this method is also implemented by the server software object that will receive the request. When the OEC library receives a request destined for this server, it unpacks the HL7 message, and delivers it to the object's getData method. To accomplish this, the server first registers the object to receive requests using Mediator.registerCallback(ke.go.moh.oec.IService)

Parameters:
requestTypeId - type of request; constant from class RequestTypeId
requestData - request data; see RequestTypeId Field Detail for descriptions
Returns:
return data; see RequestTypeId Field Detail for descriptions
